        <blockquote>
            <p class="software">
		An open source project originally designed to provide
		the University of Michigan with a secure single sign-on
		web authentication system.  Cosign is part of the
		National Middleware Initiative (NMI) <a
		href="http://www.nmi-edit.org/">EDIT</a> software
		release.
	    </p>

            <p class="software">
		See the <a href="download.html">download</a> page for
		download links, revision history, and MD5 checksums.
            </p>

            <p class="software">
            <ul>
                <li>
		    Passwords, if used, are sent only to the central
		    weblogin service over SSL.
                </li>

                <li>
		    Users need only authenticate once per session to
		    access any number of cosign-protected campus
		    sites.
                </li>

                <li>
		    A compromised service host (see the <a
		    href="overview.html">overview</a>) does not
		    represent a compromise of the
		    cosign system as a whole.
                </li>

                <li>
		    x509 users needn't enter a password to authenticate.
                </li>

                <li>
		    The cosign 'friend' system allows non umich users
		    to authenticate using self-created,
		    centrally-administered guest accounts.
                 </li>

                <li>
		    Trusted systems can request Kerberos credentials
		    from central server for N-Tier authentication (e.g.
		    IMAP, LDAP, Oracle, etc.).
                </li>

                <li>
		    There are no domain cookies used in this system.
                </li>

                <li>
		    Sessions have both idle and hard timeouts.
                </li>

                <li>
		    Users can logout of all cosign-protected services
		    by visiting a single URL.
                </li>

            </ul>
            </p>

